TERMS AND CONDITIONS
================================================================================

1. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" refers to the Omani Encyclopedia Competition Platform, including 
   all source code, documentation, assets, and associated files.

   "Substantial Modification" means changes that represent at least 40% of the 
   original codebase, including but not limited to:
   - Complete redesign of the user interface
   - Significant architectural changes
   - Addition of major new features
   - Fundamental changes to core functionality

   "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software for financial gain, including 
   but not limited to:
   - Selling the Software or access to it
   - Offering the Software as a paid service
   - Using the Software in a commercial product
   - Monetizing the Software through advertisements or subscriptions

2. PERMISSIONS

   You are free to:
   
   ✓ Use the Software for personal, educational, or non-profit purposes
   ✓ Study how the Software works and modify it
   ✓ Share copies of the Software
   ✓ Distribute your modifications under the same license
   ✓ Use the Software internally within your organization
   ✓ Deploy the Software for educational institutions (free of charge)

3. RESTRICTIONS

   You may NOT:
   
   ✗ Sell the Software or any derivative work without Substantial Modification
   ✗ Offer the Software as a commercial service without Substantial Modification
   ✗ Remove or alter copyright notices
   ✗ Use the Software name or trademarks without permission
   ✗ Sublicense the Software under different terms
   ✗ Use the Software for commercial purposes without making Substantial Modifications

4. COMMERCIAL USE REQUIREMENTS

   If you wish to use the Software commercially, you MUST:
   
   a) Make Substantial Modifications (minimum 40% of codebase changed)
   b) Clearly document all modifications made
   c) Provide attribution to the original work
   d) Release your modifications under the same license
   e) Not misrepresent the origin of the Software

5. ATTRIBUTION

   You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license, and indicate 
   if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but not in any 
   way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.

   Required attribution format:
   
   "Based on Omani Encyclopedia Competition Platform
    Original work: [repository URL]
    Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 with Commercial Restrictions"

6. SHARE-ALIKE

   If you remix, transform, or build upon the Software, you must distribute your 
   contributions under the same license as the original.

7. NO ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS

   You may not apply legal terms or technological measures that legally restrict 
   others from doing anything the license permits.

8. PATENT GRANT

   Each contributor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free patent 
